(4.1 INTRODUCTION TO CALIBRATION) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 8 Tf
50 670 Td
(The Polytron 2 XP uses a catalytic bead \(pellistor\) sensor to detect combustible gases.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 8 Tf
50 658 Td
(Accurate detection depends on periodic calibration to compensate for sensor aging, poisoning,) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 8 Tf
50 646 Td
(and environmental factors. Failure to calibrate on schedule is the leading cause of false) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 8 Tf
50 634 Td
(negatives \(failure to alarm when gas is present\) and false positives \(nuisance alarms\).) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.784 0.510 0.000 rg
BT
/FHelvB 8 Tf
50 614 Td
(4.2 CALIBRATION INTERVALS) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 8 Tf
50 596 Td
(4.2.1 Standard Calibration Schedule) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 584 Td
(  - Zero check \(bump test\): Every 30 days, or before any hot work in the monitored area.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 572 Td
(  - Full calibration \(zero + span\): Every 6 months, or after any alarm event.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 560 Td
(  - Sensor element replacement: Every 24 months, or when span calibration cannot be achieved) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 548 Td
(    within ±5% of reference gas value after two consecutive attempts.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 8 Tf
50 531 Td
(4.2.2 Accelerated Calibration Triggers) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 8 Tf
50 519 Td
(The following conditions require IMMEDIATE calibration regardless of schedule:) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 507 Td
(  \(a\) Any alarm event above 25% LEL.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 495 Td
(  \(b\) Sensor exposure to silicone vapours, lead compounds, halogenated solvents, or H2S) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 483 Td
(      concentrations above 200 ppm ? these compounds cause catalytic bead poisoning and) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 471 Td
(      permanently reduce sensor sensitivity.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 459 Td
(  \(c\) Sensor readings that drift more than ±3% LEL from known zero in a clean atmosphere.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 447 Td
(  \(d\) Any physical impact or moisture ingress to the sensor housing.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.784 0.510 0.000 rg
BT
/FHelvB 8 Tf
50 427 Td
(4.3 CALIBRATION PROCEDURE) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 8 Tf
50 409 Td
(4.3.1 Pre-Calibration Safety Requirements) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 8 Tf
50 397 Td
(IMPORTANT: Before performing calibration in a live area:) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 385 Td
(  \(a\) Obtain a Hot Work / Gas Work permit from the area supervisor.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 373 Td
(  \(b\) Verify the area reading is below 10% LEL using a portable gas detector BEFORE) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 361 Td
(      connecting calibration gas or opening the sensor housing.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 349 Td
(  \(c\) Inform the shift operator and control room of planned calibration activity.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 337 Td
(  \(d\) Have a second person present as safety observer.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 8 Tf
50 320 Td
(4.3.2 Zero Calibration) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 308 Td
(  Step 1: Connect certified zero gas \(synthetic clean air, <1 ppm HC\) at 0.5 L/min.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 296 Td
(  Step 2: Allow reading to stabilise \(minimum 2 minutes\).) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 284 Td
(  Step 3: If reading is within ±1% LEL of zero, no adjustment required. Log and sign off.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 272 Td
(  Step 4: If reading is outside ±1% LEL, adjust zero potentiometer per Figure 4-3.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 260 Td
(  Step 5: Record pre-adjustment and post-adjustment readings on Calibration Record Form CF-01.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 8 Tf
50 243 Td
(4.3.3 Span Calibration) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 231 Td
(  Step 1: Use certified reference gas at 50% LEL methane in nitrogen balance.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 219 Td
(          IMPORTANT: Reference gas cylinder must have a valid calibration certificate) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 207 Td
(          dated within the past 12 months from an accredited laboratory.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 195 Td
(  Step 2: Connect at 0.5 L/min via the sensor inlet cap \(Figure 4-4\).) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 183 Td
(  Step 3: Allow reading to stabilise \(minimum 3 minutes\).) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 171 Td
(  Step 4: Adjust span potentiometer until display reads 50.0% ±1.0% LEL.) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 159 Td
(  Step 5: If span cannot be achieved within ±5% of reference after two attempts,) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.118 0.118 0.118 rg
BT
/FCour 7.5 Tf
50 147 Td
(          sensor element requires replacement \(see Section 4.5\).) Tj
ET
0 0 0 rg
0.784 0.510 0.000 rg
